

=Definition=

''In economics, "dumping" can refer to any kind of [[Predatory Pricing]]. However, the word is now generally used only in the context of international trade law, where dumping is defined as the act of a manufacturer in one country exporting a product to another country at a [[Price]] which is either below the price it charges in its home market or is below its [[Cost]]s of production'' 
(http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dumping_%28pricing_policy%29)